Make notes:

Born in London -1926.

Catholic family and education.

Served in the war.

Entered religious life after the war.

Left, and returned to Ireland to learn law.

Became a lawyer and for the British diplomatic mission.

Went to Malaysia as a diplomat.

Met a monk in Kuala lumper

Swami sachanamda worked for peace

They talked about prayer and meditation

'more heart than mind'

Saw connections with Christian prayer and meditation.

He began to meditate with a mantra: Christian word.

Returned to Ireland, continued meditation

Entered a monastery

Gave up meditation in his routine

Studied theology in Rome

Returned to England & worked in the monastery school

Headmaster of a school in the US - late '60s

Social upheaval in society and religious life at the time

Students asked about meditation

JM researched Christian tradition found in Cassio conf. 10, the way of the 'mantra'

Tradition of the church from early church

Lawermere freeman met JM and lead him to meditation

Developed the meditation technique as a way to help others.

Died as things were beginning to change in 1982 (age 56)

LF took on the work of promoting and showing up meditation globally.
